Hi Marcin,

I could install MultiNEAT with Python 2.7 on my machine. Are you sure 
the .so library is copied to the correct place? Maybe run "ldconfig" to 
be sure Linux will find it. Also try to use Python 3.4 instead of 2.7. 
For Windows, try installing Chris Gohike's packages of MultiNEAT here: 
http://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/

Let me know if the problem persists.

Peter
